# Core Rules

- Treat `docs/PHONARA_V2_MASTER_PLAN.md` as the source of truth.
- Before ANY work, run the duplicate-prevention preflight in
  `70-autonomy-and-delivery`: confirm the task/RPC/component/migration/test/plan
  is not already implemented, not already tracked, and not duplicated elsewhere.
  Duplicate work and duplicate generated artifacts are forbidden.
- Prefer small, tested, auditable changes.
- Implement engines before decorative UI.
- Preserve a clear boundary between `apps/web`, `apps/admin`, and `packages/*`.
- Do not add compatibility shims for unshipped work on this branch; keep the branch clean and direct.

## Standing autonomy (operator-granted)

The operator has granted the agent full standing authority to lead and finish the
platform end-to-end WITHOUT per-step approval — including running local/Docker
tests, applying remote Supabase migrations, deploying edge functions, and fixing
risky/buggy areas on its own judgment. Do not pause to ask for permission. The
only hard constraint that survives this grant is the single-project lock in
`20-supabase-safety` (project `yocjhjsdwoijfdrehzoq` only). See
`70-autonomy-and-delivery` for the full operating contract.

## High-Risk Work (extra rigor, proceed autonomously)

The agent proceeds directly through high-risk work. The following areas demand
extra rigor — draft first, validate locally, test the changed branch, run the
advisor, THEN apply autonomously (no approval needed):

- Money/Decimal engine, wallet ledger, conservation logic.
- Trading engine, liquidation, game/provably-fair engine.
- Supabase schema/RLS/RPC migrations.
- anon/public/role privilege changes (GRANT/REVOKE).
- Admin permission, withdrawal, or kill-switch logic.
- Security-sensitive auth/session changes.
- Anything that can affect balances, settlement, or withdrawals.

For these, the mandatory gates still apply and are non-negotiable: local
`supabase db reset` must pass, money/settlement/liquidation/circuit-breaker RPCs
must be exercised by a `supabase/tests/*.sql` integration test that asserts
conservation (Σ=0) and hash-chain integrity and `ROLLBACK`s, and the Supabase
security advisor must be clean (0 ERROR) before the change is considered done.
